Aim

To generate delay using Timer0.

Theory
8051 has Timer0 and Timer1
TMOD selects mode
TH0/TL0 store values
TF0 indicates overflow
Timer works on machine cycle
Used for delay generation
Important in real-time systems
Simulator Used

EdSim51

Code
ORG 0000H
MOV TMOD, #01H
MOV TH0, #0FCH
MOV TL0, #018H
SETB TR0

WAIT: JNB TF0, WAIT
CLR TR0
CLR TF0

SJMP $
END
Observation
Timer started correctly
TF0 set after overflow
Delay generated successfully
Conclusion

Thus, timer-based delay was successfully generated.
